US President Donald Trump, who tested positive for Covid 19 yesterday, has been taken to hospital early on Saturday (October 3rd, 2020) after being found with mild symptoms as a result of the pandemic. Trump experienced some fatigue but has been in good spirit, according to his doctor. Trump has so far been treated with an experimental drug cocktail injection and the antiviral medication Remdesivir after both he and First Lady Melania Trump tested positive for Covid-19 on Friday. Soon after Trump and the First lady were diagnosed with COVID 19, Joe Biden who is among the presidential contestants in the US was forced to test and came out with Covid 19 negative results.